The recent Green phase highlights that `validateDamageCounts` does two things conceptually: it catches both (a) claims of more items than insured, and (b) claims for item types not insured at all (since uninsured types have count 0, and any damage > 0 exceeds 0). The error message says "exceed insured count" which is accurate but slightly misleading when the issue is "no such insured item".

## Refactoring Opportunities

Looking at the code, I see a clarity issue around `validateDamageCounts`. The function works correctly for the new characterization test (claim references item not in policy) but its error message is technically about "exceeds insured count" — for an uninsured type, this means "0 insured but >=1 damage". The intent is correct but could be clearer.

